- Everything in this file (`is_square_attacked`, `has_legal_moves`, `move_to_pgn`, cache updates, etc.) runs **only in response to human/GUI events** — a button press, a move being pushed, a redraw. Worst case you're talking about a few thousand array scans triggered a handful of times per second. On a 729 MHz Broadway core this is sub-millisecond regardless of micro-optimization.
- The actual engine's node-per-second rate (which is what "speed" means for playing strength) is determined entirely by code *not present here*. No amount of tuning in this file will move that needle.

