```

This runs up to 64 times per redraw, and `vsnprintf` re-parses the format string and does `va_arg` dispatch every time for what is just 4 known strings. Since redraws already happen at bounded intervals this isn't going to be *felt*, but it's free to fix and makes the "single buffer, single flush" design (OPT-7) actually live up to its intent:

