## Net effect

- Knight/king/pawn attack checks: hand-rolled offset arrays + per-step bounds checks → direct table reads.
- Bishop/rook/queen attack checks and move legality: O(ray length) branchy loops → O(1) magic-bitboard lookup.
- This is the same, already-validated logic the real search engine uses, so it also removes a second independently-maintained (and thus riskier) rules implementation living next to it.
- Cost: one extra `uint64_t` per `BoardState`, kept in sync with O(1) incremental updates — no per-call rebuild.


